  "body": "I gitpull latest docker image from gcr this morning, and try to start beacon node locally but error printout `runtime: out of memory`, and the deamon break out:\r\n```\r\ntime=\"2019-05-27 02:45:37\" level=info msg=\"Validator activated\" activationEpoch=0 index=255 prefix=validator\r\nfatal error: runtime: out of memory\r\n\r\nruntime stack:\r\nruntime.throw(0x132787a, 0x16)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/panic.go:617 +0x72\r\nruntime.sysMap(0xc004000000, 0x74000000, 0x2144ff8)\r\n```\r\nYou can refer to the latest complete error log as below\r\n[error.log](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/files/3221673/error.log)\r\n\r\nPS: is there any prerequisity for the testing HD environment, e.g. 1core, 1G memory with docker implementation enough? ",
